value.def: If a bird pecks at something or pecks something, it moves its beak forward quickly and bites at it.

example.ex: It was winter and the sparrows were pecking at whatever they could find...
example.tran: 时值冬季，麻雀啄食着能够找到的任何东西。

example.ex: They turn on their own kind and peck each other to death...
example.tran: 它们开始攻击同类，拼命地互相啄着。

example.ex: These birds peck off all the red flowers.
example.tran: 这些鸟啄掉了所有红色的花。

value.def: If you peck someone on the cheek, you give them a quick, light kiss.

example.ex: Elizabeth walked up to him and pecked him on the cheek...
example.tran: 伊丽莎白走到他面前，在他脸颊上匆匆吻了一下。
她轻轻地吻了一下他的脸。

example.ex: He gave me a little peck on the cheek.
example.tran: 他匆匆轻吻了一下我的脸。
